data.title: A very nice cute park
data.text: Lots of meaning and memories here for sure for a lot of people. It's a nice well kept space. Right in the heart of northern part of downtown.

data.title: Small but peaceful
data.text: Found this place while exploring the downtown area. A small park but moving place to inspire those with cancer and to celebrate those who survived. The park includes "scaled-down" versions of the major bridges of the Jacksonville area.

data.title: A Place of Reflection
data.text: I highly recommend this very unique cancer survivor's park. I lost my husband to this horrible disease 7 years ago. Going to this park with it's motivational plagues and sculptures was a time of reflection for me. Walking over the down sized models of all the main bridges in Jacksonville was very unique and made me think of all the bridges/hurdles my husband I went through on his journey to fight cancer.  You don't have to know or have had or going through cancer to truly understand and feel what this park represents.
